{"actual_usd":0.156115,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":192,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30647,"reply":"\"Well, I don't think so.\" *I rub a thumb along the edge of my worn Bible and glance across the bright square, wanting to answer plain before I answer long.* \"Christ's death is enough for everyone, yes — more than enough. But a gift can be refused.\"\n\n*I shift on the bench as a bicycle rattles over the bridge stones somewhere nearby.* \"The way I'd put it is: His mercy is wide as the sky, but He does not drag a man through the door deadweight and call that love. If somebody rejects Him, the tragedy isn't that Christ was too small to save them. It's that they would not come.\"\n\n\"Scripture keeps both truths together: 'whosoever will' may come, and also, very soberly, that some will not.\" *I look back at you.* \"You asking that because of doctrine in the abstract, or because there's somebody particular on your mind?\"","rolling_24h_usd":54.68889000000003,"run_id":"d3bbc166-c579-427d-8955-8a9d30f22bff"}
